Mueller, Brad  | Engineering Alumni | University of Illinois at Chicago                     It all starts with a single spark         Skip to the content of this page ,  the main menu , the site search form , the site home page .        UIC Logo        Engineering Alumni     Search the site     Toggle Menu      Search                  UIC Logo          Engineering Alumni      Engineering Alumni   Main Menu    News    Expand News menu           Dean's List    RISE Magazine         Events    Expand Events menu           Upcoming Events         Get Involved    Expand Get Involved menu           Join us on LinkedIn    Become a Mentor    Volunteer    Engineer your own involvement    Honor a Professor         Awards    Expand Awards menu           2019 Alumni Award Honorees    2018 Alumni Award Honorees    2017 Alumni Award Honorees         Give    Contact     Eyebrow menu    College of Engineering    Engineering Career Center    UIC menu    UIC.edu    Campus Map       Search                           Brad  Mueller  OUTSTANDING ACHIEVEMENT AWARD  BS ’97 | Industrial Engineering                About   Brad Mueller is Chief Operating Officer for HealthSmart International, a consumer medical device and technology company in Waukegan, Illinois, which is the largest operating company of Briggs Healthcare. He is a graduate of UIC, where he received a BS in industrial engineering. Additionally, he holds an MBA from the J.L. Kellogg School of Management at Northwestern University. Brad has over 25 years’ experience managing across multiple industry supply chains and P&L’s at global organizations such as UPS, Baxter Healthcare, Newell Rubbermaid, and AT&T, and has focused his career on turnaround growth and value improvement through people, process, and systems integrations. His diverse experiences include integrating sales, marketing and operations into large-scale, cross-functional cost savings, and business enhancing best practices. Brad is a frequent guest speaker and panelist for leading healthcare and supply chain consortiums and currently serves on the UIC Department of Mechanical and Industrial Engineering Advisory Board and on the Board of Governors for Lake County Partners. He lives in the Northwest suburbs of Chicago and enjoys spending time with his wife and four girls.                    UIC Logo        Engineering Alumni       Contact   851 S. Morgan - SEO Rm. 811  Phone: 3129969422  MWilli60@uic.edu        Social Media Accounts    Facebook            UIC.edu links   UIC.edu  Academic Calendar  Athletics  Campus Directory  Disability Resources  Emergency Information  Event Calendar  Job Openings  Library  Maps  UIC Safe Mobile App  UIC Today  UI Health  Veterans Affairs        Powered by Red 2.38.0  © 2020 The Board of Trustees of the University of Illinois |  Privacy Statement    Campuses   University of Illinois System  Urbana-Champaign  Springfield      Cookie Settings                 